    "tree_id": "b9af10c7d5b87dd9406117de7bdac4fc2130c639",
    "message": "Harden send path: always surface \"insufficient -> consolidate\", never mask as internal error (v1.6.4)\n\nRoot cause of \"balance is enough but can't send + scary 程序内部出错\": a\nfragmented mining wallet's spend fails as InsufficientBalance (the 6-note\nper-tx cap), which should route to the consolidation prompt. But that\nfailure (or a null amount, or an analytics hiccup) could surface as a THROWN\nexception and get shown as a generic internal error, masking the real,\nactionable guidance. v1.6.2 hardened only the analytics calls before the\nflow; this closes the remaining gaps.\n\n- SendViewModel.send(): replace `zatoshiAmount!!` with an explicit, friendly\n  guard; wrap the onEach updateMetrics/reportFailures in runCatching so\n  reporting can never break the transaction stream.\n- SendFragment.runSend(): on a caught throwable, scan the whole cause chain\n  for \"insufficient\" and route to NeedConsolidate instead of a generic error\n  (full stack trace still logged for pinpointing genuine internal bugs).\n- SendScreen: clarify the consolidation guidance — \"balance is enough, just\n  too fragmented; max 6 notes per send; nothing was spent\".\n\nBalance \"doesn't match\" is the displayed *available* (spendable, witness-at-\nanchor, 10-confirmation) balance legitimately differing from total; the home\ncard already shows the gap as 待确认 +X. No balance math change.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
    "timestamp": "2026-06-16T04:55:14Z",
